OL,3,CMum admits stealing #15,000 from two
OL,4,Cresidents while working at care home
OL,6,FOne involves fraud by dishonestly
OL,7,Fmaking a false representation, namely
OL,8,Fthat she had permission to use a bank
OL,9,Fcard in a man's name.
OL,11,FA second crime relates to the theft of
OL,12,F#9,414.80 from the man.
OL,14,FGregson's offending occurred during a
OL,15,Fperiod of nine months, between 3 April
OL,16,F2023 and 8 January 2024.
OL,18,FEarlier this year, Gregson pleaded
OL,19,Fguilty to charges of fraud and theft
OL,20,Frelating to a different care home
OL,21,Fresident.
